        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2394939401" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1009149914326196464">This was one where I, like the rest of Goodreads (why can&apos;t the devs figure this out?) wish I could give half stars. I would have gone 3.5, not quite a 4 for me.<br/><br/>Sweet story, standard &quot;i&apos;m not like other girls! I wanna be FREE!&quot; story. Put together well and not overly religious but the themes are there. <br/><br/>I couldn&apos;t get over Trip&apos;s high and mighty attitude at times to be honest though. Really Trip? you&apos;ve never told a lie? you&apos;ve never made a mistake? Get over yourself.<br/><br/>Also couldn&apos;t figure out how </span>
  <span id="freeText1009149914326196464" style="display:none">This was one where I, like the rest of Goodreads (why can't the devs figure this out?) wish I could give half stars. I would have gone 3.5, not quite a 4 for me.<br /><br />Sweet story, standard "i'm not like other girls! I wanna be FREE!" story. Put together well and not overly religious but the themes are there. <br /><br />I couldn't get over Trip's high and mighty attitude at times to be honest though. Really Trip? you've never told a lie? you've never made a mistake? Get over yourself.<br /><br />Also couldn't figure out how the villain got so villian-y. He seemed to go from 0-60 really fast without a lot of backstory explaining how he became who he was, which would have been nice.<br /><br />Even with those two points that I didn't love I thought it was fun. Marguerite was a treat. Her chemistry with Trip was great and there was enough action throughout to keep it entertaining. Overall, sweet read. Good for a summer relaxing day. If you like clean Christian romance this should be right up your alley!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1009149914326196464" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

